      <section class="heritage">
	<div class="dynamic-title">
	  <h2 id="dynamicText">Born at AFRL, Hardened at Pratt & Whitney, Ready for Production.</h2>
	</div>
	
	<div class="heritage-details">
	  <div class="heritage-text">
	    <p>
              <strong>FEMORPH</strong> was conceived and developed at the 
              <strong>Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL)</strong> to address the challenge of modeling 
              as-manufactured geometries with simulation-grade accuracy. 
	    </p>
	    <p>
              The technology has been <strong>hardened in collaboration with Pratt & Whitney</strong>, 
              where it has demonstrated robust performance across industrial-scale use cases in 
              digital twin creation, mesh adaptation, and optimization workflows.
	    </p>
	    <p>
              FEMORPH is now <strong>ready for production deployment</strong> in aerospace, energy, and 
              advanced manufacturing environments.
	    </p>
	  </div>
	  
